1
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:52,620
=Endless Love=

2
00:00:52,620 --> 00:00:55,540
=Episode 14=

3
00:01:00,359 --> 00:01:01,759
My Lady, you're awake.

4
00:01:05,400 --> 00:01:06,319
Where am I?

5
00:01:08,200 --> 00:01:09,200
Who are you?

6
00:01:10,280 --> 00:01:12,719
My Lady, I serve you.

7
00:01:13,319 --> 00:01:15,079
I'm your maidservant, Ke'er.

8
00:01:15,400 --> 00:01:16,400
Ke'er...

9
00:01:18,159 --> 00:01:19,640
Such a familiar name.

10
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:22,159
But

11
00:01:22,760 --> 00:01:24,920
I don't remember anything.

12
00:01:26,400 --> 00:01:27,719
Then what is my name?

13
00:01:29,280 --> 00:01:29,799
My Lady,

14
00:01:30,159 --> 00:01:32,159
your name is Liu Rushi.

15
00:01:32,560 --> 00:01:35,159
You are the daughter
of the Liu family, a merchant household.

16
00:01:35,640 --> 00:01:38,200
Unfortunately, your father,
Mr. Liu, passed away so early,

17
00:01:38,519 --> 00:01:40,519
and now only your mother

18
00:01:40,879 --> 00:01:43,359
runs the family business
in the south of the city.

19
00:01:43,879 --> 00:01:44,400
Yes, that's it.

20
00:01:49,959 --> 00:01:51,760
If you're truly feeling unwell,

21
00:01:51,920 --> 00:01:52,760
then don't push yourself.

22
00:01:54,799 --> 00:01:56,040
What exactly happened?

23
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:58,200
Just a small accident.

24
00:01:59,959 --> 00:02:01,239
The porridge is being cooked.

25
00:02:01,599 --> 00:02:03,599
I'll have to tell you
the rest another time.

26
00:02:19,719 --> 00:02:21,080
I'm fed up with these memorials!

27
00:02:21,560 --> 00:02:22,520
I want Lanpingmei and Dongxiangji!

28
00:02:22,599 --> 00:02:23,199
Give them to me!

29
00:02:24,120 --> 00:02:24,919
You are the King of this land,

30
00:02:24,919 --> 00:02:26,039
yet you read that kind of filth?

31
00:02:26,319 --> 00:02:27,080
Don't you read them?

32
00:02:28,120 --> 00:02:29,000
Are you done?

33
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,439
Who are you people?

34
00:02:31,120 --> 00:02:32,159
Who am I?

35
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,879
I've told you a thousand times,

36
00:02:35,120 --> 00:02:36,680
you are the King of Xiling.

37
00:02:36,800 --> 00:02:38,120
No, I don't believe it!

38
00:02:38,560 --> 00:02:40,159
I don't want to be the King of Xiling

39
00:02:40,159 --> 00:02:41,000
and be locked up in here!

40
00:02:41,000 --> 00:02:43,560
I want to go out and have fun!

41
00:02:45,639 --> 00:02:46,400
Go away.

42
00:02:46,800 --> 00:02:47,560
Out of my sight.

43
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:48,439
I hate you.

44
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:49,800
Your Majesty.

45
00:02:50,520 --> 00:02:51,919
You will understand soon.

46
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:01,840
Remember,

47
00:03:02,199 --> 00:03:03,360
no matter what His Majesty asks,

48
00:03:03,520 --> 00:03:04,560
how he pressures you,

49
00:03:05,039 --> 00:03:06,879
you must never speak of Mu Ruyi.

50
00:03:08,360 --> 00:03:10,280
If His Majesty dwells on it too much,
I fear

51
00:03:10,439 --> 00:03:11,360
that his madness will intensify.

52
00:03:12,240 --> 00:03:13,120
Understood.

53
00:03:13,319 --> 00:03:14,840
Additionally, spread the word

54
00:03:15,159 --> 00:03:16,520
that the King has fallen critically ill

55
00:03:17,039 --> 00:03:18,080
and is in no condition to govern.

56
00:03:18,919 --> 00:03:20,080
Whoever disobeys this
shall be put to death.

57
00:03:20,520 --> 00:03:21,000
Yes.

58
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,360
(One month ago)
(Your Highness!)

59
00:03:22,759 --> 00:03:24,080
(One month ago)
(Thankfully, they are out of danger.)

60
00:03:24,479 --> 00:03:25,879
(But they both have head injuries,)

61
00:03:25,960 --> 00:03:26,879
(which is why they're unconscious.)

62
00:03:30,439 --> 00:03:30,919
(It's here.)

63
00:03:31,759 --> 00:03:33,439
(My heart is half an inch off
from where it belongs.)

64
00:03:34,120 --> 00:03:35,960
(If you want to take my life,
then do it.)

65
00:03:36,120 --> 00:03:37,599
(If you fail to save Her Highness,)

66
00:03:38,280 --> 00:03:39,639
(I will take your life.)

67
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:42,159
(As you wish.)

68
00:03:49,280 --> 00:03:49,960
(What is it?)

69
00:03:50,560 --> 00:03:51,840
(At critical moments, this pill)

70
00:03:52,479 --> 00:03:54,360
(is used for clearing
and expelling stagnant blood.)

71
00:03:54,520 --> 00:03:56,080
(Then why not give it to Her Highness?)

72
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:57,719
(Its effects are potent.)

73
00:03:57,960 --> 00:03:59,159
(Through it can promote blood circulation
and remove stasis,)

74
00:03:59,319 --> 00:04:00,319
(addressing the immediate crisis,)

75
00:04:00,759 --> 00:04:03,080
(those who take it
will suffer mental confusion)

76
00:04:03,319 --> 00:04:05,080
(and lose
some critical emotional memories.)

77
00:04:05,240 --> 00:04:08,240
(In ancient texts,
this herb is called the Oblivion Herb.)

78
00:04:08,719 --> 00:04:09,800
(Forget about the memories!)

79
00:04:10,120 --> 00:04:10,879
(Life is what matters.)

80
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:16,600
(I never knew
such a miraculous herb could exist.)

81
00:04:17,120 --> 00:04:17,959
(Forget the love,)

82
00:04:18,199 --> 00:04:19,639
(and people can be cured.)

83
00:04:20,120 --> 00:04:22,279
(Thankfully, her twins were saved.)

84
00:04:22,560 --> 00:04:23,920
(But her temperament
has changed drastically.)

85
00:04:24,240 --> 00:04:26,759
My Lady, put down those pirated books.

86
00:04:27,199 --> 00:04:28,639
The porridge is ready. Come.

87
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,279
(Shuixu Brothers)
Shuixu Brothers.

88
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:41,800
(Bride Snatch to the West)
Bride Snatch to the West.

89
00:04:42,399 --> 00:04:43,720
(Drill of the Three Kingdoms)
Drill of the Three Kingdoms.

90
00:04:44,160 --> 00:04:45,519
These are all my favorite books!

91
00:04:45,920 --> 00:04:47,000
Mind your own business.

92
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:49,800
And you, Xia Ke'er.

93
00:04:50,439 --> 00:04:52,000
Who sent you here?

94
00:04:52,399 --> 00:04:53,639
I have porridge in the morning,

95
00:04:53,759 --> 00:04:54,720
at noon,

96
00:04:54,879 --> 00:04:55,879
and at night.

97
00:04:56,639 --> 00:04:58,079
Do I look like porridge to you?

98
00:05:00,720 --> 00:05:02,439
You've just recovered
from a serious illness.

99
00:05:02,439 --> 00:05:04,040
Greasy food is not good for you.

100
00:05:04,560 --> 00:05:05,360
Just make do for now.

101
00:05:09,560 --> 00:05:11,959
I suspect you're not my maidservant.

102
00:05:12,519 --> 00:05:13,720
You trade in human lives.

103
00:05:14,199 --> 00:05:15,800
You won't even give me a bite of meat,

104
00:05:15,959 --> 00:05:17,680
and you want to sell me off
for a good price!

105
00:05:17,920 --> 00:05:19,879
If I wanted to sell you
for a good price,

106
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,759
I'd have to keep you nice and plump.

107
00:05:22,519 --> 00:05:24,720
So you really do want to sell me!

108
00:05:24,959 --> 00:05:26,600
With your talent for making things up,

109
00:05:26,839 --> 00:05:28,759
you could be a storyteller
at a teahouse!

110
00:05:30,639 --> 00:05:32,360
Great idea.

111
00:05:38,920 --> 00:05:40,759
Time to treat myself to some meat!

112
00:05:43,399 --> 00:05:44,759
I'm going crazy!

113
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:46,680
Did your memory just come bouncing back

114
00:05:46,680 --> 00:05:47,959
like a performing monkey's?

115
00:05:53,399 --> 00:05:55,680
Your Highness,
His Majesty is unwell today

116
00:05:55,879 --> 00:05:56,680
and is taking a nap.

117
00:05:56,920 --> 00:05:58,360
Did he mention the details?

118
00:05:59,759 --> 00:06:00,680
He said...

119
00:06:01,519 --> 00:06:02,759
He said...

120
00:06:15,519 --> 00:06:16,120
Your Majesty.

121
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:18,199
Your Majesty!

122
00:06:22,160 --> 00:06:22,759
Your Highness.

123
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:25,240
His Majesty put on a eunuch's clothes

124
00:06:25,439 --> 00:06:26,519
and slipped out of the palace.

125
00:06:26,759 --> 00:06:28,879
You're all going to give me
a heart attack one day.

126
00:06:29,199 --> 00:06:31,800
Your Highness,
aren't you skilled in medicine yourself?

127
00:06:32,279 --> 00:06:33,639
A physician cannot heal themselves.

128
00:06:34,639 --> 00:06:35,560
What are you waiting for?

129
00:06:36,040 --> 00:06:37,519
I'll find an imperial physician
right away.

130
00:06:37,720 --> 00:06:38,759
What is wrong with you?

131
00:06:39,839 --> 00:06:41,279
Find His Majesty now!

132
00:06:44,279 --> 00:06:45,000
Boss!

133
00:06:48,480 --> 00:06:49,319
Miss, please have a seat.

134
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:51,720
Do you have silkworm pupae,
centipedes, or scorpions?

135
00:06:51,839 --> 00:06:52,839
I'll have a pound of each.

136
00:06:55,399 --> 00:06:57,319
Miss, I don't have enough money

137
00:06:57,519 --> 00:06:58,480
to make change for this.

138
00:06:59,160 --> 00:07:00,399
Today is your lucky day.

139
00:07:00,600 --> 00:07:01,360
Buy yourself a drink.

140
00:07:02,800 --> 00:07:04,120
I'll be honest with you,

141
00:07:04,360 --> 00:07:05,399
the last portion of the silkworm pupae

142
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:07,360
has already been served
to that gentleman.

143
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,279
Take all the money,

144
00:07:11,399 --> 00:07:12,160
and I want the pupae.

145
00:07:12,879 --> 00:07:13,439
Miss,

146
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,319
when people run a business,

147
00:07:15,319 --> 00:07:16,720
they follow the principle
of first come, first served.

148
00:07:16,959 --> 00:07:18,720
It's not about who is richer.

149
00:07:19,279 --> 00:07:21,480
These pupae are mine today.

150
00:07:21,680 --> 00:07:22,279
Is all my money

151
00:07:22,279 --> 00:07:23,759
enough to make me
"first come, first served"?

152
00:07:24,680 --> 00:07:25,920
What a beggar!

153
00:07:26,160 --> 00:07:27,240
What are you?

154
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,120
Boss,

155
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:29,759
open your eyes

156
00:07:30,319 --> 00:07:31,079
(Eunuch of Imperial Stables)
and see for yourself.

157
00:07:31,079 --> 00:07:31,900
(Eunuch of Imperial Stables)

158
00:07:33,000 --> 00:07:34,279
Here you go, sir!

159
00:07:34,560 --> 00:07:35,000
Please enjoy!

160
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,240
What are you so cocky about?

161
00:07:36,759 --> 00:07:38,319
It's just a piece of wood.

162
00:07:39,319 --> 00:07:40,240
Do you really think I don't know it?

163
00:07:40,720 --> 00:07:41,879
Seriously?

164
00:07:42,279 --> 00:07:44,199
My money could buy an entire pig.

165
00:07:44,399 --> 00:07:45,120
Are you sure you won't take it?

166
00:07:45,639 --> 00:07:46,560
If you're so rich,

167
00:07:46,720 --> 00:07:48,240
go buy a pig and eat it raw!

168
00:07:48,600 --> 00:07:49,720
Dear guests, please calm down.

169
00:07:49,839 --> 00:07:51,079
Cool it off.

170
00:07:52,160 --> 00:07:52,800
Your Majesty...

171
00:07:53,079 --> 00:07:54,240
I...

172
00:07:54,399 --> 00:07:55,560
Do you know the token he's holding?

173
00:07:55,560 --> 00:07:56,240
Your Majesty,

174
00:07:56,360 --> 00:07:58,120
why did you slip out
in a eunuch's dress?

175
00:07:58,240 --> 00:07:59,480
We've been searching everywhere for you.

176
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:00,920
Who sent you here?

177
00:08:01,199 --> 00:08:02,079
Prince Mo said

178
00:08:02,480 --> 00:08:03,839
you're not allowed
to leave the palace freely.

179
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,839
Is he above me?

180
00:08:05,959 --> 00:08:07,680
Miss, do you know who he is?

181
00:08:07,839 --> 00:08:09,079
Who? Just tell me already.

182
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:11,399
He's a eunuch from the palace.

183
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,079
A eunuch? What is that?

184
00:08:14,199 --> 00:08:15,000
A eunuch is

185
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:16,839
a man who has been castrated

186
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,680
and then brought into the palace
to serve.

187
00:08:18,920 --> 00:08:20,839
They can never have children

188
00:08:20,959 --> 00:08:22,240
or share a bed with a woman.

189
00:08:22,519 --> 00:08:23,680
They are living a hard life.

190
00:08:24,000 --> 00:08:25,560
Oh, how pitiful.

191
00:08:26,800 --> 00:08:28,959
He lost his manhood from a young age.

192
00:08:28,959 --> 00:08:30,639
No wonder he's so petty.

193
00:08:30,959 --> 00:08:31,839
Keep running your mouth,

194
00:08:31,879 --> 00:08:33,000
and you'll end up as a eunuch.

195
00:08:33,440 --> 00:08:34,120
But...

196
00:08:34,240 --> 00:08:35,360
Leave!

197
00:08:35,720 --> 00:08:36,240
Go!

198
00:08:37,279 --> 00:08:38,240
Why are you so unreasonable?

199
00:08:38,399 --> 00:08:39,440
This is mine!

200
00:08:39,919 --> 00:08:40,559
Mister!

201
00:08:40,960 --> 00:08:41,440
No,

202
00:08:41,639 --> 00:08:42,600
sister!

203
00:08:42,799 --> 00:08:43,960
How about we share?

204
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:46,279
Who says I wanted to share with you?

205
00:08:46,440 --> 00:08:47,080
Give it back!

206
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:59,039
Who are you, really?

207
00:09:00,799 --> 00:09:02,200
Why would I tell you?

208
00:09:02,919 --> 00:09:04,399
You look quite  familiar.

209
00:09:05,320 --> 00:09:05,960
Have you

210
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,200
ever crossed me before?

211
00:09:09,039 --> 00:09:10,919
If it weren't for the fact
that you're a sister,

212
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,279
I would have beaten you already.

213
00:09:13,440 --> 00:09:14,919
You are talking nonsense.

214
00:09:15,080 --> 00:09:15,879
Shameless!

215
00:09:16,919 --> 00:09:18,600
I'm shameless?

216
00:09:20,279 --> 00:09:22,080
There's plenty more I don't know.

217
00:09:23,200 --> 00:09:24,480
How about you show me?

218
00:09:26,080 --> 00:09:26,720
You...

219
00:09:27,519 --> 00:09:29,200
But you might disappoint me

220
00:09:29,480 --> 00:09:32,159
since you're not complete at all.

221
00:09:33,120 --> 00:09:34,600
What are you rambling about?

222
00:09:36,759 --> 00:09:38,919
Eunuch, you dropped your badge.

223
00:09:39,279 --> 00:09:41,120
Eunuch? What do you mean?

224
00:09:41,840 --> 00:09:43,120
Isn't this your badge?

225
00:09:43,399 --> 00:09:45,039
An imperial eunuch! Such a noble status!

226
00:09:45,039 --> 00:09:47,039
Boss, I'll return the plate next time!

227
00:09:48,480 --> 00:09:49,600
You pupa thief!

228
00:09:49,879 --> 00:09:51,039
Pray you don't get caught by me!
